# Crypto Tarot Project Rules for Cursor AI

## Project Context
This is a crypto-themed tarot card reading web application. It's a single-page application with 78 cards (22 Major Arcana + 56 Minor Arcana).

## Code Style
- Use ES6 modules (import/export)
- Prefer single quotes for strings
- Use camelCase for variables and functions
- Use descriptive names that reflect crypto/tarot theme
- Format code with Prettier (configured in .prettierrc)

## File Structure
- `data/card-meanings.js` - Canonical source of truth for all card data
- `script.js` - Main application logic
- `js/` - Utility modules (spread types, combinations, history, AI service, card-utils)
- `scripts/build/` - Build scripts (cardmap, book generation)
- `scripts/game/` - Game mechanics scripts
- `scripts/export/` - Export scripts (PDF, Markdown, LaTeX)
- `scripts/fix/` - One-time fix scripts (archived)
- `scripts/utils/` - Utility scripts
- `assets/` - Images, cardmap.json, etc.
- `print/book/` - Generated book files
- `docs/` - Documentation (guides, status, development)

## Key Conventions
- Card images: `tools/CryptoTarot1-78/major-{title}-{number}.jpg` or `minor-{rank}-of-{suit}-{number}.jpg`
- Card IDs: Use `fileSafe()` function to convert titles to IDs
- Image resolution: Use `getCardImagePath(card)` function for consistent image paths
- Card data structure: Each card in CARD_MEANINGS has: title, type, suit, upright, reversed, bookChapter, etc.

## Important Functions
- `getCardImagePath(card)` - Resolves card image path using hash-based variant selection
- `fileSafe(name)` - Converts card titles to file-safe IDs
- `buildDeck()` - Creates the full 78-card deck
- `resolveCardImage(card)` - Resolves card image with cardmap.json fallback

## When Editing
- Always update `data/card-meanings.js` for card data changes
- Run `npm run generate:cardmap` after adding new card images
- Use `npm run format` before committing
- Test in browser at `http://localhost:8000`
- Use shared utilities from `js/card-utils.js` (fileSafe, getCardImagePath, escapeHtml)

## AI/LLM Context
- This is entertainment only, not financial advice
- Crypto terminology should be accurate but accessible
- Tarot meanings should blend traditional tarot with crypto concepts

## Common Patterns
- Cards are objects with: `{ id, title, type, suit, img, borderColor }`
- Major Arcana: type='Major', suit='Major'
- Minor Arcana: type='Minor', suit is one of: Tokens, Wallets, Blocks, Nodes
- Card meanings come from `CARD_MEANINGS[card.title]`

